{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 20:01:38.262692", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Short answer – the network is healthy.**  \\nAll 64 ping tests returned 2\\u202f/\\u202f2 packets with 0\\u202f% loss, so every host can reach both `pc_1_2` (10.1.2.2) and `pc_0_4` (10.0.4.2).  No packet drops or time‑outs were observed.\\n\\n**What the numbers tell us**\\n\\n| Host | Destination | Avg RTT (ms) | Jitter (ms) | Notes |\\n|------|-------------|--------------|-------------|-------|\\n| pc_0_0 … pc_3_7 | pc_1_2 | 1.6\\u202f–\\u202f5.6 | 0.12\\u202f–\\u202f3.1 | All within a few ms of each other; the highest is 5.6\\u202fms (pc_2_0). |\\n| pc_0_0 … pc_3_7 | pc_0_4 | 1.6\\u202f–\\u202f4.1 | 0.006\\u202f–\\u202f1.6 | All within a few ms; the highest is 4.1\\u202fms (pc_3_7). |\\n\\n* **No packet loss** – every ping succeeded.\\n* **Low latency** – the average round‑trip times are all under 6\\u202fms, which is well within the expected range for a local‑area network.\\n* **Acceptable jitter** – the standard deviation (jitter) is generally below 1\\u202fms; the few outliers (e.g., 2.33\\u202fms jitter on pc_2_7 to pc_0_4) are still tiny compared to the mean RTT.\\n\\n**Potential “issues” that are not actually problems**\\n\\n* **Higher RTT on some paths** – e.g., pc_2_0 to pc_1_2 averages 5.6\\u202fms, a bit higher than the rest of the hosts.  This is still a perfectly normal value for a multi‑hop path through a few switches; it does not indicate a failure.\\n* **Occasional spikes** – a few pings show a single high RTT (e.g., 8.7\\u202fms on pc_2_0 to pc_1_2).  These are isolated spikes and do not affect overall connectivity.\\n\\n**Conclusion**\\n\\nThe ping matrix shows a fully connected, loss‑free network.  All hosts can reach both target PCs, and the latency/jitter figures are within normal limits for a LAN.  No further troubleshooting is required at this time., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='00d01259-ad88-464a-ac7b-780ab417bbe6'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
